Hi, I have been using Emacs since about 2014 or 2015.

I have a personal website, where I sometimes post about Emacs: https://amodernist.com/.

== Packages ==

Here are a few packages on mine which I have contributed to ELPA or MELPA:

* [http://elpa.gnu.org/packages/setup.html setup] (see SetupEl)
* [http://elpa.gnu.org/packages/shell-command+.html shell-command+]
* [http://elpa.gnu.org/packages/vc-backup.html vc-backup]
* [http://elpa.gnu.org/packages/compat.html compat]
* [https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/autocrypt.html autocrypt]
* [https://melpa.org/#/clang-capf clang-capf]
* [https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/face-shift.html face-shift]
* [https://melpa.org/#/insert-kaomoji insert-kaomoji]
* [https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/xref-union.html xref-union]
* [https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/site-lisp.html site-lisp]
* [https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/openpgp.html openpgp]
* [https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/auto-header.html auto-header]
* [https://elpa.gnu.org/packages/do-at-point.html do-at-point]


I am also an occasional contributor to core Emacs (https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs.git/log/?qt=author&q=philipk%40posteo.net), GNU ELPA (https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs/elpa.git/log/?qt=author&q=philipk%40posteo.net) and NonGNU ELPA (https://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs/nongnu.git/log/?qt=author&q=philipk%40posteo.net).

== Misc ==

In the modernisation debate I am on the traditional side, and prefer OOTB behaviour.

You can find me IRC (libera.chat) with the username pkal.

You might also find me on the EmacsMailingLists emacs-devel and help-gnu-emacs.

I have an Emacs-related account on the [https://emacs.ch/@pkal fediverse].

